TY  - JOUR
AU  - Liu, Yang
AU  - Zhou, Guofu
AU  - Zhu, Yingzi
T1  - Trend Factor in China: The Role of Large Individual Trading
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raae003
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 14
IS  - 2
SP  - 348
EP  - 380
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We propose a novel trend factor for the Chinese stock market that incorporates both price and volume information to capture dominant individual trading, momentum, and liquidity. We find that volume plays a more significant role in the trend factor for China than for the United States, reflecting the greater retail participation in China. By incorporating this trend factor into the 3-factor model of Liu et al. (2019), we propose a 4-factor model that explains a wide range of stylized facts and 60 representative anomalies. Our study highlights the important role of individual trading in asset pricing, especially in China. (JEL G12, G14, G15)
Y2  - 6/6/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raae003
ER  - 



